◆ CarToSpDEval()

void ChronusQ::CarToSpDEval ( SHELL_EVAL_TYPE  typ,
size_t  L,
double *  fCarEVal,
double *  FSpEVAl,
size_t  IOff,
size_t  IOffSCR,
bool  forceCart 
)

Basis Set transformation from Cartesian to Spherical it also provide to copy to the final storage (pointer) and requires that the transformation matrix Sp <-> Cart is already populated.

Basis Set Cartesian to Sperical conversion over a single shell. It needs to be called also for cartisian evaluation, since this function handles the final population of the eval Storage for the shell and points.

Parameters
[in]typType of evaluation to perform (gradient, etc)
[in]LAngular quantum momentum
[in]fCarEValeval Storage for the shell set evaluation, f(ixyz,iSh,ipt). Variable dimensions(npts*NBasisEff*1 or 4) allocated outside. This storage will have all values of the functions in the shell, for each shell, for each point. If requested there will be appended f/dx(ixyz,iSh,ipt), f/dy(ixyz,iSh,ipt), f/dz(ixyz,iSh,ipt) values of the functions in the shell, for each shell(nShSize), for each point(npts)
[in/out]fEval eval Storage for the shell set evaluation, f(ixyz,iSh,ipt). Variable dimensions(npts*NBasisEff*1 or 4) allocated outside. This storage will have all values of the functions in the shell, for each shell, for each point. If requested there will be appended f/dx(ixyz,iSh,ipt), f/dy(ixyz,iSh,ipt), f/dz(ixyz,iSh,ipt) values of the functions in the shell, for each shell(nShSize), for each point(npts)
[in]IOffOffSet to properly store the basis set and Gradient components
[in]IOffSCROffSet to properly read the basis set in cartesian and Gradient components..
[in]forceCartTrue if force cartesian, otherwise sperical evaluation
Here is the caller graph for this function:

◆ constructEPCZVars()

void ChronusQ::constructEPCZVars ( bool  electron,
DENSITY_TYPE  denTyp,
size_t  NPts,
double *  CVgammaEval,
double *  ZgammaVar3 
)

Construct the required quantities for the formation of the Z vector, for a given density component, given the kernel derivatives wrt U variables.

See J. Chem. Theory Comput. 2011, 7, 30973104 (modified e derived for Scalar and Magn).

Parameters
[in]dentypType of 1PDM (SCALAR, {M_k}).
[in]isGGAWhether to include GGA contributions.
[in]NPtsNumber of points in the batch
[in]VRhoEvalPointer to the first partial derivative of the energy per unit volume in terms of the dens[+,-].
[in]VgammaEvalPointer to the first partial derivative of the energy per unit volume in terms of the gammas[++,+-,–].
[out]ZrhoVar1Factors to multiply the scalar density for particular Z matrix
[out]ZgammaVar1Factors to multiply the gradient scalar density for particular Z matrix
[out]ZgammaVar2Factors to multiply the gradient particular mag density for particular Z matrix

Note we build 2 * X in Eq 12 and 13 in J. Chem. Theory Comput. 2011, 7, 30973104. Since ZMAT LDA part needs to factor 0.5 for the symmetrization procedure (see Eq. 15 1st term on r.h.s) ZrhoVar1 part does not need this factor anymore.

The 0.5 factors come from the chain rules.

On the other hand since we are building 2 * X, we factor already in both ZgammaVar1 and ZgammaVar2 (since there is 0.5 coming from the chain rules as well for the GGA terms). Note there is still a factor of 2 that is included already in the Grad SCALAR/Mz (the one required in Eq 17).

Notes. The ZrhoVar1 multiply the LDA contribution to ZMAT

Notes. The ZgammaVar1 multiply the GGA Del SCALAR contribution to ZMAT Notes. The ZgammaVar2 multiply the GGA Del Mk contribution to ZMAT

Here is the caller graph for this function:

Sorts a vector of eigenvalues in a standard way.

Assigns a standard ordering for both real and complex eigenvalues. Initially sorts by magnitude, then by the real part to ensure a consistant ordering between conjugate pairs if they exist.

Sorts a vector of eigenvalues relative to a particular value in a standard way.

Assigns a standard ordering for both real and complex eigenvalues relative to their distance from a provided shift value. Initially sorts by magnitude of the distance, then by the real part of the distance to ensure a consistant ordering between conjugate pairs if they exist.

[in/out]W Eigenvalues to sort. On exit contains sorted eigenvalues

◆ evalShellSet() [1/4]

void ChronusQ::evalShellSet ( CQMemManager &  memManager,
SHELL_EVAL_TYPE  typ,
std::vector< libint2::Shell > &  shells,
double *  pts,
size_t  npts,
double *  fEval,
bool  forceCart 
)

Level 1 Basis Set Evaluation Function.

Evaluates a shell set over a specified number of cartesian points.

Level 1 Basis Set Evaluation Function (only for debug) Evaluates a shell set over a specified number of cartesian points. All distances of the points from each shell origin are computed and used in the Level 2 Basis Set Evaluation Function

Parameters
[in]memManagerCQ memory manager (for allocate distances inside)
[in]typType of evaluation to perform (gradient, etc)
[in]shellsShell set for evaluation(vector of libint2::Shell).
[in]ptsRaw storage of the cartesian points (dimension 3 * npts)
[in]nptsNumber of cartesian points to evaluate.
[in/out]fEval eval Storage for the shell set evaluation, f(ixyz,iSh,ipt). Variable dimensions(npts*NBasisEff*1 or 4) allocated outside. This storage will have all values of the functions in the shell, for each shell, for each point. If requested there will be appended f/dx(ixyz,iSh,ipt), f/dy(ixyz,iSh,ipt), f/dz(ixyz,iSh,ipt) values of the functions in the shell, for each shell(nShSize), for each point(npts)

void ChronusQ::evalShellSet ( SHELL_EVAL_TYPE  typ,

)

Level 3 Basis Set Evaluation Function.

Level 3 Basis Set Evaluation Function Evaluates a single shell over a single cartesian point. This function requires a precomputed the distance and its x,y,z components for the point from the shell origin. An offset to properly store the results can be used.

Evaluates a single shell over a single cartesian point. This function requires a precomputed

distance and its x,y,z components for the point from the shell origin. An offset

to properly store the results can be used..

Parameters
[in]typType of evaluation to perform (gradient, etc)
[in]shellShell for evaluation(libint2::Shell).
[in]rSqRaw storage of square distance between the point and the shell origin (precomputed outside)
[in]rRaw storage of x,y,z of the vector between each point and the shell origin (precomputed outside).
[in/out]SCR eval Storage for the shell set evaluation, f(ixyz,iSh,ipt). Variable dimensions(npts*NBasisEff*1 or 4) allocated outside. This storage will have all values of the functions in the shell, for each shell, for each point. If requested there will be appended f/dx(ixyz,iSh,ipt), f/dy(ixyz,iSh,ipt), f/dz(ixyz,iSh,ipt) values of the functions in the shell, for each shell(nShSize), for each point(npts)
[in]IOffSCROffSet to properly store the basis set.

Level 2 Basis Set Evaluation Function.

Level 2 Basis Set Evaluation Function - Used in the KS - DFT Evaluates a shell set over a specified number of cartesian points. This function requires a precomputed set of the distances and their x,y,z component for each point from each shell origin in the shells vector.

Evaluates a shell set over a specified number of cartesian points. This

function requires a precomputed set of distances and their x,y,z components

for each point from each shell origin in the shells vector..

Parameters
[in]typType of evaluation to perform (gradient, etc)
[in]shellsShell set for evaluation(vector of libint2::Shell).
[in]evalshellsVector of bool to know if that Shell is relevant for evaluation.
[in]rSqRaw storage of overall squared distances between each point and the shell origin (precomputed outside) Dimension (nshells * npts)
[in]rRaw storage of overall x,y,z of the vector between each point and the shell origin (precomputed outside). Dimension (3*nshells*npts)
[in]nptsNumber of cartesian points to evaluate.
[in]nCenterNumber of total distint shell center (is NAtoms).
[in]NBasisEffNumber of basis function to be evaluated given all the shells in input.
[in]mapSh2CenShell Mapping to atom centers.
[in/out]fEval eval Storage for the shell set evaluation, f(ixyz,iSh,ipt). Variable dimensions(npts*NBasisEff*1 or 4) allocated outside. This storage will have all values of the functions in the shell, for each shell, for each point. If requested there will be appended f/dx(ixyz,iSh,ipt), f/dy(ixyz,iSh,ipt), f/dz(ixyz,iSh,ipt) values of the functions in the shell, for each shell(nShSize), for each point(npts)
[in]SCReval Storage for the shell set evaluation, Cartesian f(MaxShellSize).
[in]IOffSCRoffset for eval Storage for the shell set evaluation, Cartesian f(MaxShellSize).
[in]forceCartTrue if force cartesian, otherwise sperical evaluation

template<typename MatsT >
void ChronusQ::formZ_vxc ( std::shared_ptr< PauliSpinorSquareMatrices< MatsT > >  onePDM,
DENSITY_TYPE  denTyp,

double *  Hy,
double *  Hz,
double *  BasisScratch,
double *  ZMAT 
)

assemble the final Z vector -> ZMAT (for a given density component), given the precomputed required U dependent quantities (ZUvar# from constructZVars) and the V variables (DenS/Z/X/Y and GDenS/Z/Y/X from evalDen) in input. It requires in input also the pointer (BasisScratch) to all basis set (and their gradient)

See J. Chem. Theory Comput. 2011, 7, 30973104 (modified e derived for Total and Magn)

Parameters
[in]isGGAWhether to include GGA contributions
[in]NPtsNumber of points in the batch
[in]NBEEffective number of basis to be evalauted (only shell actives)
[in]IOffOffset used for accessing all basis set (and their gradient)
[in]epsScreenScreening tollerance
[in]weightsQuadrature weights
[in]ZrhoVar1Factors to multiply the scalar density for particular Z matrix
[in]ZgammaVar1Factors to multiply the gradient scalar density for particular Z matrix
[in]ZgammaVar2Factors to multiply the gradient particular mag density for particular Z matrix
[in]DenSPointer to the V variable - SCALAR
[in]DenZPointer to the V variable - Mz
[in]DenYPointer to the V variable - My
[in]DenZPointer to the V variable - Mx
[in]GDenSPointer to the V variable - Gradient X,Y,Z comp of SCALAR
[in]GDenZPointer to the V variable - Gradient X,Y,Z comp of Mz
[in]GDenYPointer to the V variable - Gradient X,Y,Z comp of My
[in]GDenZPointer to the V variable - Gradient X,Y,Z comp of Mx
[in]BasisScratchPointer to Basis set evaluated over batch of points.
[out]Pointerto the ZMAT.

Note. See Documentations of constructZVars.

Smart wrapper around DGEEV and ZGEEV depending on context.

Templated function which diagonalizes a general (non-hermetian) matrix which is general to real and complex. Handles memory managment internally through a CQMemManager object. Always returns complex eigenvalues for generality.

See http://www.netlib.org/lapack/lapack-3.1.1/html/dgeev.f.html or http://www.netlib.org/lapack/lapack-3.1.1/html/zgeev.f.html for parameter documentation.

◆ getLWork()

template<typename T >
int ChronusQ::getLWork ( std::function< void(T *, int *)>  func)

Helper function to obtain optimal LAPACK workspace dimension.

Parameters
[in]funcFunction which returns the optimal workspace
Returns
Optimal workspace dimension

z.B.

For DSYEV, the optimal workspace may be queried by passing LWORK = -1 (like all LAPACK functions). The parameter list for DSYEV is given as

void dsyev_(char *JOBZ, char *UPLO, int *N, double *A, int *LDA, double *W, double *WORK, int *LWORK, int *INFO);

To use this function to query the workspace, we may bind a set of arguments to the funcion (i.e. the parameters from a DSYEV envocation)

auto test = std::bind(dsyev,&JOBZ,&UPLO,&N,A,&LDA,W, std::placeholders::_1, std::placeholders::_2,&INFO);

And then get the worksapce

int LWORK = getLWork<double>(test);

inline

Initialize the ChronusQ environment.

Sets up to the environment for a ChronusQ calculation. Currently initialized the libint2 environment and sets the default thread pool to a single thread (serial calculation)

◆ libintGeneralContractionERI()

std::pair< size_t, double > ChronusQ::libintGeneralContractionERI ( size_t  P,
size_t  Q,
size_t  R,
size_t  S,
BasisSet &  basisSet,
libint2::Engine &  engine,
std::vector< std::vector< libint2::Shell > > &  shellPrims_,
std::vector< double * > &  coefBlocks_,
double *  workBlock,
const double *&  resPQRS 
)
inline

Compute ERI in a general-contraction shell quartet. Note layout difference, resPQRS need to be reorganized by the following code to match the layout of a general shell quartet output as in libcint: for (size_t SS = 0, pqrs = 0; SS < sContrSize; SS++) for (size_t s = 0; s < sAMSize; s++) for (size_t RR = 0; RR < rContrSize; RR++) for (size_t r = 0; r < rAMSize; r++) for (size_t QQ = 0; QQ < qContrSize; QQ++) for (size_t q = 0; q < qAMSize; q++) for (size_t PP = 0; PP < pContrSize; PP++) for (size_t p = 0; p < pAMSize; p++, pqrs++) { block[pqrs] = resPQRS[(s + sAMSize * (r + rAMSize * (q + qAMSize * p)))

  • pqrsAMSize * (PP + pContrSize * (QQ + qContrSize * (RR + rContrSize * SS)))]; }
    Returns
    The count of engine.compute2 calls, and the total time of such calls

wrapper for evaluating and loading the NEO-DFT kernel derivatives from libxc wrt to the U var.

Note. We compute all the quantities for all points in the batch.

Parameters
[in]NPtsNumber of points in the batch
[in]DenPointer to the Uvar Density vector[+,-].
[in]GammaPointer to the GGA Uvar vector[++,+-,–].
[in]aux_DenPointer to the auxiliary Uvar Density vector[+,-].
[in]aux_GammaPointer to the auxiliary GGA Uvar vector[++,+-,–].
[out]epsEvalPointer to the energy per unit particle.
[out]VRhoEvalPointer to the first part der of the energy per unit volume in terms of the dens[+,-].
[out]VgammaEvalPointer to the first part der of the energy per unit volume in terms of the gammas[++,+-,–].
[out]CVgammaEvalPointer to the first part der of the energy per unit volume in terms of the gammas[++,+-,–].
[out]EpsSCRPointer for multiple functional eval. See epsEval
[out]VRhoSCRPointer for multiple functional eval. See VRhoEval
[out]VgammaSCRPointer for multiple functional eval. See VgammaEval

◆ LUInv() [1/2]

template<typename _F >
int ChronusQ::LUInv ( int  N,
_F *  A,
int  LDA,
CQMemManager &  mem 
)

Computes the inverse of a non-singular matrix A. Initially computes the LU factorization then wraps DGETRI / ZGETRI for the matrix inversion depending on context.

See http://www.netlib.org/lapack/lapack-3.1.1/html/dgetri.f.html or http://www.netlib.org/lapack/lapack-3.1.1/html/zgetri.f.html for parameter documentation.

◆ MatAdd() [1/18]

template<typename _F1 , typename _F2 , typename _F3 , typename _FScale1 , typename _FScale2 >
void ChronusQ::MatAdd ( char  TRANSA,
char  TRANSB,
size_t  M,
size_t  N,
_FScale1  ALPHA,
const _F1 *  A,
size_t  LDA,
_FScale2  BETA,
const _F2 *  B,
size_t  LDB,
_F3 *  C,
size_t  LDC 
)

Add two (sub) matricies together.

C = ALPHA * op(A) + BETA * op(B)

Parameters
[in]TRANSADefines op(A)
[in]TRANSBDefines op(B)
[in]MNumber of rows in A and B
[in]NNumber of columns in A and B
[in]ALPHAScaling parameter which scales A
[in]ARaw storage of the matrix A
[in]LDALeading dimension of the matrix A
[in]BETAScaling parameter which scales B
[in]BRaw storage of the matrix B
[in]LDBLeading dimension of the matrix B
[in/out]C Raw storage of the matrix C
[in]LDCLeading dimension of the matrix C

op(A) and op(B) are defined the same as for GEMM operations with the addition the 'R' will yield a pure conjugation (not conjugate transpose as in 'C') of a complex matrix

Warning
It is only possible for A/C or B/C to overlap if op(A) or op(B) are 'N', respectively.
Here is the caller graph for this function:

◆ PairTransformation() [10/10]

template<typename ATyp , typename TTyp , typename BTyp >
void ChronusQ::PairTransformation ( char  TRANST,
const TTyp *  T1,
size_t  LDT1,
size_t  OffK,
const TTyp *  T2,
size_t  LDT2,
size_t  OffL,
char  TRANSA,
const ATyp *  A,
size_t  NI,
size_t  NJ,
size_t  NM,
char  TRANSB,
BTyp *  B,
size_t  NK,
size_t  NL,
ATyp *  ASCR,
BTyp *  SCR,
bool  increment 
)

Transform tensor A with transformation matrix T1 and T2 in pair (first two dim of A)

B(K, L, M) = T1(I, K+OffK)^H A(I, J, M) @ T2(J, L+OffL)

Parameters
[in]TRANSAWhether transpose/adjoint A as A(IJ, M) before transformation
[in]DIDimension of index I in A
[in]DJDimension of index J in A
[in]DMDimension of index M in A
[in]ATensor before transformation
[in]TRANSTWhether transpose/adjoint T1 and T2
[in]T1Transformation matrix T1
[in]LDT1Leading dimension of T1
[in]OffKoffset in index K
[in]T2Transformation matrix T2
[in]LDT2Leading dimension of T2
[in]OffLoffset in index L
[in]TRANSBWhether transpose/adjoint B as B(KL, M) after transformation
[in]DKDimension of index K in B
[in]DLDimension of index L in B
[out]BTensor after transformation, can be same as A
[in]ASCRScratch space for A at least NI*NJ*NM of ATyp. Only reference when TRANSA != 'N'
[in]SCRScratch space for intermediates, at least NJ*NM*NK of BTyp.
[in]incrementPerform B += result if true
Here is the call graph for this function:
Here is the caller graph for this function:

◆ TransformLeft() [1/9]

template<typename Apha , typename ATyp , typename BTyp , typename CTyp >
void ChronusQ::TransformLeft ( size_t  M,
size_t  N,
size_t  KA,
size_t  KB,
Apha  alpha,
ATyp *  A,
size_t  LDA,
std::vector< BTyp * >  V,
size_t  LDB,
CTyp *  SCR,
std::vector< CTyp * >  U,
size_t  LDC 
)

Multiply a series of matrices on the right with a given matrix.

C_i = \alpha AB_i for all B_i in V

If the matrices are of different dimension, the A matrix is assumed to be tensored with the appropriate identity matrix to give the dimension of the A matrix.

e.g.

B = | a b | A = | e | --> C = | ea eb | | c d | | ec ed |

Parameters
[in]MNumber of rows in A
[in]NNumer of columns in B
[in]KANumber of columns in A
[in]KBNumber of rows in B. Must be a multiple of KA.
[in]alphaScalar in multiplication
[in]APointer to A
[in]LDALeading dimension of A
[in]VVector of pointers to B matrices
[in]LDBLeading dimension of B
[in]SCRScratch space, at least M*N. Only referenced if any B_i is the same as any C_i
[out]UVector of pointers to C matrices. Can be the same as V.
[out]LDCLeading dimension of C
Here is the call graph for this function:
